content: I'm planning a trip to the nearby state park and want to know the best time to spot Bald Eagles. I've seen them before on a guided bird walk, but I'd love to observe them on my own. Do you have any information on their nesting habits and when they're most active? By the way, on my way back from the beach last month, I stopped at a wildlife refuge and saw a flock of Snow Geese, which were migratory birds I had never seen before.
